comment: LATR shows that Porter (WAS) and Wall (WAS) maintain legal guarding position as they contest Knight's (PHO) shot attempt.
Tucker (PHO) makes body contact with Wall (WAS) that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Morris (PHO) makes contact with Porter's (WAS) body while he is in the act of shooting his made layup attempt.
Morris (PHO) sets the screen on Sessions (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Porter (WAS) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Beal (WAS) makes incidental contact with Tucker (PHO) that does not affect his FOM or ability to catch the entry pass.
Beal (WAS) sets the screen on Morris (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RATR shows that Price (PHO) establishes legal guarding position, but that Beal (WAS) does not go through the space of the defender. Any contact is considered incidental.
LATR shows that Wall (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Knight's (PHO) drive and layup attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release by Temple (WAS) is considered incidental.
LATR shows that Porter (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Bledsoe's (PHO) driving layup attempt.
Price (PHO) reaches in for the steal and makes body contact with Beal (WAS).
Beal (WAS) makes contact with Knight's (PHO) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Phoenix is correctly assessed a Delay of Game for not taking their positions in between free throw attempts.
Phoenix is correctly assessed a technical foul for their 2nd Delay of Game for not taking their spots in between free throw attempts.
Tucker (PHO) commits a take foul on Temple (WAS).
